STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    1328 "Destroyed"
    1330 "Red held"
    1331 "Contended"
    1332 "UN held"
    1333 "Approaching Red Interceptors interrupt a UN fighter-bomber strike against a key communist target. The UN Force consists of one squadron of strike aircraft, one squadron tasked with flak suppression and another on fighter escort duty. Two enemy squadrons face them.\n\nClick the UN or Red button to view details of each squadron. Click on a pilot icon to select the duty you wish to perform during the mission.\n"
    1334 "A squadron of UN medium bombers rumbles across the skies of North Korea. Ahead, fighter-bombers drop down to suppress flak batteries around the mission target. Above, fighter escort aircraft react to the sudden appearance of communist interceptor aircraft.\n\nClick the UN or Red button to view details of each squadron. Click on a pilot icon to select the duty you wish to perform during the mission.\n"
    1335 "A UN fighter squadron performing a sweep in MiG Alley discovers an incursion by a squadron of enemy fighters. Neither side has the distinct advantage so both jostle for position.\n\nClick the UN or Red button to view details of each squadron. Click on a pilot icon to select the duty you wish to perform during the mission.\n"
    1336 "While patrolling in MiG Alley, a UN fighter squadron encounters a squadron of enemy interceptors. Each time this scenario is played out, the positional advantage will be set at random.\n\nClick the UN or Red button to view details of each squadron. Click on a pilot icon to select the duty you wish to perform during the mission.\n"
    1337 "A UN fighter patrol finds its catch of the day: a squadron of enemy fighter aircraft has crossed into MiG Alley at a lower altitude where UN jets perform best. The UN patrol is placed above and to the rear of its foe.\n\nClick the UN or Red button to view details of each squadron. Click on a pilot icon to select the duty you wish to perform during the mission.\n"
    1338 "Finding few Red aircraft willing to drop down to the lower altitudes that UN aircraft favor, a squadron of UN fighters forces a conflict by patrolling at high altitude. They are bounced by a Communist squadron that comes screaming in from behind and above.\n\n Click the UN or Red button to view details of each squadron. Click on a pilot icon to select the duty you wish to perform during the mission.\n"
    1339 "A UN armed-reconn mission searches the area along the main highway for enemy supply trucks. Enemy fighters may be patrolling in the local area.\n\nClick the UN button to view details of the aircraft performing the mission duty.\n"
    1340 "A UN armed-reconn mission risks heavy ground fire by searching the main rail-line for enemy locomotives. Enemy interceptors may patrol this area.\n\nClick the UN button to view details of the aircraft performing the mission duty.\n"
    1341 "Communist Forces launch an air-strike against a key UN facility. A UN patrol nearby reacts to the attack.\n\nClick the UN or Red button to view details of each squadron. "
    1342 "Admire the Korean landscape without enemy interference.\n\nClick the UN button to view details of the aircraft performing the mission duty.\n"
    1343 "A UN fighter-bomber squadron expects heavy flak as it performs a strike against a key target south of 'MiG Alley'.\n\nClick the UN button to view details of the aircraft performing the mission duty.\n"
END
