    1344 "You are entering the landing pattern at a new airfield. The Tower has instructed you to land, then taxi around and take off. Repeat this process as many times as you like. The runway has been cleared for your use."
    1345 "Communist Forces occupying Seoul have established a bridge-head south of the Han River. Additional Red Forces are crossing by boat to open up the front. We have no forward air control in this area but you are cleared to engage any targets found along the banks of the Han.\n\nClick the UN button to view details of the aircraft performing the mission duty.\n"
    1346 "During combat over the Yalu, a UN pilot becomes separated from his flight. Before he can exit the arena he happens across a lone Red fighter in a similar situation. Tactical advantage is randomly determined each time this scenario is played out.\n\nClick the UN or Red button to view details of each squadron. Click on a pilot icon to select the duty you wish to perform during the mission.\n"
    1347 "A UN pilot finds himself in an ideal firing position behind a red fighter. The Chinese pilot is slow to react to the threat.\n\nClick the UN or Red button to view details of each squadron. Click on a pilot icon to select the duty you wish to perform during the mission.\n"
    1348 "A UN armored patrol is approaching the town of Hoengsong via the southern road. Enemy troops have occupied the ridge that overlooks the town and are laying mortar fire onto the convoy. Try to conserve your rockets. T-34 Tanks may exit the town to directly engage the column. You will make your approach from the north. No FAC is available.\n\nClick the UN button to view details of the aircraft performing the mission duty.\n"
    1350 "Novice"
