    24002 "Dis is the title"
    24003 "DIS is the body text"
    24004 "IX CORPS MAKES FINAL STAND"
    24005 "UN positions North of Chonan are coming under attack from Chinese troops. They must not be pushed back from this line."
    24006 "IX CORPS FACES ASSAULT"
    24007 "Forces have engaged on a line between Suwon and Osan."
    24008 "REDS CROSS HAN"
    24009 "The enemy have established a bridge-head and are currently engaging positions south of the Han. More troops are crossing the river by boat."
    24010 "CHINESE ATTACK IX CORPS"
    24011 "The Taeryong River is a natural boundary that the Reds must cross if they are to take their objective, Munsan-ni."
    24012 "UN launch offensive"
    24013 "A major UN offensive has been launched on the IX Corps front. The local division is reporting resistance as it pushes towards the village of Pyongtaek."
    24014 "New IX Corps Offensive"
    24015 "A major UN offensive has been launched on the IX Corps front. Our troops are attempting to move up the main highway to capture Suwon."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24016 "UN launch offensive"
    24017 "We have launched a new ground offensive in the west sector. Our forces are attempting to dislodge enemy defenders south of the Han River so that a push into Seoul can be made."
    24018 "IX Corps offensive underway"
    24019 "An IX Corps offensive is being held up by Chinese resistance in an area north-west of Munsan-ni."
    24020 "New IX Corps operation"
    24021 "IX Corps troops are fighting northwards with the aim of capturing Pyongsan."
    24022 "UN attack Pyongyang"
    24023 "IX Corps forces south of Pyongyang are expecting fierce resistance today as they launch an all out assault on the North's Capital."
    24024 "X Corps push towards Wonju"
    24025 "Major UN operations are being conducted in the area south of Wonju. X Corps commanders are confident that this key supply point can be taken."
    24026 "X Corps launches new attacks"
    24027 "Our troops have struck out from Wonju to meet the main line of resistance just south of Hoengsong."
    24028 "UN offensive in central sector"
    24029 "UN forces in this area are eager to break through the Chinese lines and take the key town of Chuncheon."
    24030 "New X Corps offensive"
    24031 "X Corps forces are fighting across difficult terrain in this region. The main hotspots are between Chuncheon and the Hwachon Reservoir."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24032 "X Corps attacks Iron Triangle"
    24033 "X Corps has launched an offensive in an area known as the Iron Triangle; a hilly region bounded by Pyonggang, Kumwha and Chorwon."
    24034 "X Corps: Final assault"
    24035 "X Corps is engaged in what it hopes will be a final and decisive operation to outflank forces defending the Northern capital."
    24036 "REDS FINAL PUSH!"
    24037 "The reds have attacked our last line of defense south of Wonju. We must hold them back or the UN will be pushed out of Korea."
    24038 "X CORPS DEFENDS"
    24039 "The U.S. 23rd Infantry Regiment and a French battalion are holding the mountain ringed village of Chipyong-ni, some 10 miles Northwest of Wonju. They are being surrounded by enemy forces."
    24040 "ENEMY OFFENSIVE"
    24041 "A major Red offensive has been launched on the line running south of Chuncheon."
    24042 "NEW RED ASSAULT"
    24043 "Reds are attempting a new push south from their line at Hwachon."
    24044 "CHINESE OFFENSIVE LAUNCHED"
    24045 "The Chinese have amassed enough supplies to launch and sustain a major new offensive. The battle is taking place in an area called the Iron Triangle."
    24046 "NEW ENEMY PUSH"
    24047 "The Reds have snatched potential victory away from us by mounting a push southwards, away from their last line of defense."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24048 "UN move north to new line"
    24049 "Following their defeat in this sector, Red Troops across the country have withdrawn northwards. The bomb-line now runs from Suwon to Hoengsong. All targets north of this line are Chinese held."
    24050 "Reds assault X Corps sector"
    24051 "The Communists have withdrawn to a new line that passes through Seoul, Chuncheon and Yangyang."
    24052 "UN advance"
    24053 "Our Forces' victory has pushed the Communists back to a new continuous line running through Kaesong and Hwachon."
    24054 "UN move forward"
    24055 "Following their rapid withdrawal and our swift advance, Red Forces have occupied new positions on a continuous front running from Sariwon to Pyonggang."
    24056 "Enemy pushed to final line"
    24057 "The Communists have ceased their northward flight and are preparing to face UN Forces advancing towards their Capital."
    24058 "Communists advance"
    24059 "Country-wide, UN Forces have dropped back to a new line. Chinese forces are pursuing as quickly as they can."
    24060 "UN DEFEND WEST LINE"
    24061 "The Reds are attacking to the north-west of Pyongsan."
    24062 "Commonwealth troops arrive"
    24063 "British troops will be arriving in South Korea today to participate in the UN defense."
END
