STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24064 "Supplies stockpiled"
    24065 "Supplies are being stockpiled at this location. We recommend a strike as soon as possible."
    24066 "Supply to enemy front restricted"
    24067 "Interdiction sorties are successfully limiting the number of supplies that replenish this front. Poorly armed and under-nourished enemy soldiers have been surrendering to our forward patrols."
    24068 "Enemy supplies getting through"
    24069 "We believe that the enemy have more than adequate supplies in this area. They seem capable of matching our Force's ammunition expenditure during artillery exchanges. We must step up our interdiction efforts."
    24070 "CAS missions effective"
    24071 "FACs on this front report that close air support missions have severely punished enemy ground forces."
    24072 "Red offensive feared"
    24073 "Activity along this front indicates that the Reds may be preparing to launch a new assault."
    24074 "UN forces flanked"
    24075 "The situation on this front has become untenable and our Forces are attempting to pull back before they are trapped."
    24076 "Red offensive repulsed"
    24077 "Our forward units report that Chinese Forces have ceased attacking and are moving back to their line of departure. The Sector Commander is confident that the attack has been repulsed and the line can be stabilized."
    24078 "Enemy pull back to re-supply"
    24079 "Chinese troops have suddenly broken contact and are racing back to their prepared positions. The Local Commander believes that their supplies were insufficient to sustain the assault. "
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24080 "All UN Corps withdraw to new line"
    24081 "The collapse of UN resistance on this front has resulted in all friendly forces abandoning this line and falling back to prepared reserve positions."
    24082 "UN Forces preparing for offensive"
    24083 "A UN offensive in this sector is being planned. A major interdiction effort against the MSR will create the ideal conditions for an assault on this front."
    24084 "UN offensive succeeds"
    24085 "Chinese Forces in this sector have been defeated. All Red Forces along this line are making a tactical withdrawal to a new reserve line. UN Ground Forces are rapidly consolidating their gains."
    24086 "UN offensive aborted"
    24087 "The Local Commander reports unacceptably high UN losses in this sector. The order to disengage from combat and abort the current offensive has been issued."
    24088 "FAC requests urgent CAS"
    24089 "Mosquito pilots report fierce combat in this sector. They claim that without immediate and substantial air support, UN ground units will suffer severe losses."
    24090 "Friendly-fire incident"
    24091 "UN troops claim that they are suffering unnecessary casualties due to pilots making inaccurate strikes against targets close to their positions."
    24092 "Battle progressing well"
    24093 "Our Forces are making good gains on this front. The enemy's main line of defense has been broken."
    24094 "AAA increase along rail-lines"
    24095 "Intelligence division has noted a serious increase in the number of anti-aircraft defenses along the main rail-lines routes."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24096 "AAA increase at supply points"
    24097 "The volume of anti-aircraft fire encountered at enemy supply points has increased significantly."
    24098 "AAA increase along roads"
    24099 "AAA coverage along main roads and highways has reached a new and disturbing level."
    24100 "AAA increase at bridges"
    24101 "The Reds have increased flak coverage at all major bridges and choke points."
    24102 "Fake bomb craters on runway"
    24103
                            "Circular rings of dirt are arranged on the runway to give the impression that severe damage was inflicted during prior air attacks. We have noted that these fake craters do not always match the size and pattern of real craters, and so can be identified."
    24104 "Bridge spans hidden during day"
    24105
                            "A night reconn team has turned in an interesting report. Before dawn, the reds remove and hide spans from the bridge, creating the impression that the bridge is down. At night, the spans are replaced to allow traffic across."
    24106 "Unacceptable B29 losses"
    24107 "Our medium bomber losses are unacceptable. Until further notice, all B29 squadrons are standing down from duty."
    24108 "B29s back on duty"
    24109 "Our B29s are available for duty again. Ensure that you protect them adequately or you will lose their services again."
    24110 "Situation critical"
    24111 "Communist forces have infiltrated to the rear to set up roadblocks. The situation has become critical. UN Forces remaining at the front risk being cut off from supplies and support."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24112 "Truck deception discovered"
    24113
                            "One of our pilots has uncovered another example of Red ingenuity. To avoid detection and attack from the air, some communists have attached thatched roofs to their supply trucks. From a distance, stationary vehicles look like huts."
    24114 "Another strange report"
    24115
                            "It seems that the enemy will resort to any method to get supplies to their front. A pilot has reported chasing ammo porters disguised as monks. Upon hitting one of the fellows the pilot was greeted with a massive secondary explosion."
    24116 "Allies pull back"
    24117 "Our defeat in a key sector has thrown the entire allied line back to old positions."
    24118 "UN retreat to new line"
    24119 "The Reds have pushed our entire defensive line southwards to new positions."
    24120 "Bridges repaired quickly"
    24121 "Repair materials are being stored nearby so repairs can be undertaken immediately."
    24122 "Xx"
    24123 "Xx"
    24124 "Rail interdiction effective"
    24125 "Our interdiction efforts against the communist rail net are proving effective. Recent reconn shows that there is little change in the number of boxcars at principal marshalling yards, signifying that they are unable to move out."
    24126 "Under threat"
    24127 "Enemy forces are dangerously close to this airfield. Staff and crews are prepared to evacuate key equipment and aircraft the instant you issue the order."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24128 "Reds gain control"
    24129 "The enemy now controls this airfield."
    24130 "UN gain control"
    24131 "This airfield is now in UN hands. Our maintenance crews are moving in to ready the field for use."
    24132 "Reds employing huge labor force"
    24133 "The enemy makes good use of its huge civilian labor force. It takes the same amount of time to fill one hundred craters as it does to fill one."
    24134 "MiGs appear"
    24135 "MiGs have appeared over the Yalu in great numbers."
    24136 "Enemy Squadrons arrive"
    24137 "Enemy Squadrons have taken up residence on the airfield. The field is fully operational."
    24138 "Emergency Evacuation"
    24139 "This airfield has been rapidly evacuated in response to the increasingly close proximity of enemy Ground Forces. Staff are unhappy that some equipment has been left behind."
    24140 "IX CORPS ATTACKED"
    24141 "The enemy are making a major effort to push UN troops away from their Capital."
    24142 "Squadrons leave"
    24143 "Enemy squadrons have pulled out of this airfield."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24144 "Abandoned"
    24145 "This airfield has been abandoned. The enemy does not have enough resources to maintain the base while under constant pressure from air strikes."
    24146 "Fake aircraft found"
    24147 "We have discovered that this airfield is actually non-operational. The field has been set up with dummy aircraft that appear real from a distance. The enemy obviously intend for us to expend resources hitting a target of little military value."
    24148 "Enemy using damaged warehousing"
    24149 "Reconn shows that the enemy are using damaged warehousing for storage."
    24150 "New Aircraft Arrived"
    24151 "A new batch of aircraft have arrived from the States. Your most depleted squadron will receive up to four new aircraft."
    24152 "Jolson arrives"
    24153 "Al Jolson has arrived in Korea to entertain the troops. Order your tickets now."
    24154 "New MiG squadron sighted"
    24155 "We have noted the arrival of a new MiG squadron. We believe that an existing squadron has been rotated out en masse, much to our advantage."
    24156 "MiG Squadron training"
    24157 "We have noted there is an entire MiG squadron that has little desire to face our fighters. On the occasions when they enter MiG Alley they will not descend to engage."
    24158 "MISSION 1 BRIEFING"
    24159 "The NKAF is posing a serious threat. On June 27, 2 Yaks strafed Kimpo airfield, hitting the tower, a fuel dump and a C54 transport plane.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nYou are ordered to perform an armed-reconn mission along the main rail-line leading into Seoul from Munsan-ni.\n"
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24160 "MISSION 2 BRIEFING"
    24161 " MISSION BRIEF:\nFollow the northern road from Wonju to Hoengsong and engage any traffic.\n "
    24162 "MISSION 3 BRIEFING"
    24163 " MISSION BRIEF:\nPatrol the area between Suwon and Osan and engage North Korean support columns.\n "
    24164 "MISSION 4 BRIEFING"
    24165 "Patrol the highway between Osan and Pyongtaek. Enemy columns are pushing rapidly through this area."
    24166 "-"
    24167 "-"
    24168 "-"
    24169 "-"
    24170 "MISSION 1 BRIEFING"
    24171 "At least five NKA divisions are reportedly massing near Wagewan, 20 miles north west of Taegu. They may have tank support.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nHit the enemy units before they deploy against our front line positions.\n"
    24172 "MISSION 2 BRIEFING"
    24173 "The enemy assault is now underway in the Taegu sector. NKA forces are attempting to drive a wedge between the ROK 1st and 6th Divisions.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nFly close air support along the Taegu front.\n"
    24174 "MISSION 3 BRIEFING"
    24175 "A regiment of the US 24th Division is being dispatched to this sector to bolster the defense.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nFly Close Air Support.\n"
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24176 "MISSION 4 BRIEFING"
    24177 "Elements of the British 27th brigade have arrived in Korea. Battalion from the Middlesex Regiment and the Argyll and Sutherland Highlanders are being deployed north of Taegu.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nFly Close Air Support.\n"
    24178 "-"
    24179 "-"
    24180 "-"
    24181 "-"
    24182 "MISSION 1 BRIEFING"
    24183 "MISSION BRIEF:\nYou are tasked with destroying a Supply Facility.\n"
    24184 "MISSION 2 BRIEFING"
    24185 "MISSION BRIEF:\nYour target is a key river crossing.\n"
    24186 "MISSION 3 BRIEFING"
    24187 "Premier Chou En-Lai has warned the United Nations that China will come to the aid of North Korea if the latter's territory is invaded.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nDestroy a Supply Dump\n"
    24188 "MISSION 4 BRIEFING"
    24189 "MISSION BRIEF:\nAttack a warehouse facility.\n"
    24190 "MISSION 5 BRIEFING"
    24191 "MISSION BRIEF:\nAttack a warehouse facility.\n"
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    24192 "MiniText17_H"
    24193 "MiniText17_M"
    24194 "MISSION 1 BRIEFING"
    24195 "We believe Sinuiju to be the seat of Kim Il Sung's Fugitive Government.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nFly cover for a B29 raid on this important city.\n"
    24196 "MISSION 2 BRIEFING"
    24197 "Increasing numbers of Chinese 'volunteers' are entering North Korea. We have authorization to attack the bridges linking Sinuiju with Antung in China.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nPatrol the Yalu and prevent Chinese MiGs from interfering with our B-29 attack against the Yalu bridges.\n"
    24198 "MISSION 3 BRIEFING"
    24199 "It appears that our intelligence greatly underestimated the number of Chinese Troops already present in Korea.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nPerform a MiGCAP along the Yalu River.\n"
    24200 "MISSION 4 BRIEFING"
    24201 "Chinese Forces have launched shock attacks against our troops. The entire 8th army is reeling backwards under the weight of superior numbers.\n\nMISSION BRIEF:\nPatrol the area opposite Antung and hold back any intruding MiGs. Our bombers are concentrating against targets all along the Yalu.\n"
    24202 "MISSION 5 BRIEFING"
    24203 "MISSION BRIEF:\nFly a barrier patrol along the Yalu to the Northeast of Sinuiju.\n"
    24204 "MISSION 6 BRIEFING"
    24205 "MISSION BRIEF:\nMaintain air superiority over Sinuiju while our medium bombers make another attempt against the Yalu bridges.\n"
    24206 "MiniText24_H"
    24207 "MiniText24_M"
END
