STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    2200 "target descriptions"
    2201 "The Twin Yalu bridges link the gateway city of Sinuiju with Antung in China. The road and combination road/rail bridges are heavily defended. During winter the Yalu River often freezes to the point where heavy goods can be carried across the ice."
    2202 "One road and one rail bridge (close and almost parallel) cross a branch of the Yalu River south of Sinuiju en route to Yomju. The bridges have some wooden components."
    2203 "This road bridge lies in a valley between Kanggye and Pungsan. It is mainly constructed from timber."
    2204 "A single road bridge crosses the Yalu further inland where the river is narrower. This solid construction carries the road to Huichon."
    2205 "A large double track rail bridge and one small road bridge cross the Taeryong River north of Sinanju."
    2206 "Two steel-trestle rail bridges cross the river Chongchon to the north side of Sinanju. A highway bridge crosses further up river to the east."
    2207 "This is a reinforced highway bridge in the rolling hills just north of Kimchaek."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    2208 "One road and one rail bridge cross a fork in the river just south of Tanchon on the east coast. The less sturdy road bridge is at the end of the northern fork."
    2209 "This single track rail bridge spans a large valley near Pukchong. The bridge has six spans and three concrete supports."
    2210 "This solid rail bridge crosses the Kumjinchon River on the East Coast."
    2211 "This wooden rail bridge is constructed in the difficult terrain south of Manpo."
    2212 "This reinforced rail bridge is in the hills south of Kangye."
    2213 "The Nan-gang River is crossed by a single wooden rail bridge in the hills east of the northern capital."
    2214 "This concrete and steel rail bridge sits in the heart of Pyongyang City. It consists of eighteen steel spans."
    2215 "This road bridge is situated in a fairly mountainous wooded area near Chuncheon."
    2216 "Two solidly engineered road bridges lie in the center of Pyongyang city."
    2217 "This large double track rail bridge crosses the Han-gang River just to the north west of Munsan in a slightly hilly area. The bridge has fifteen steel spans and fourteen concrete support struts."
    2218 "A small wooden rail bridge spans the river just south of Yonhung. This bridge has only four spans and two supports."
    2219 "A small wooden single track rail bridge crosses a river to the south of Yonhung on the East Coast."
    2220 "A small wooden single track rail bridge spans the Imjin River in quite a hilly area."
    2221 "A large concrete road bridge spans the Han-gang River on Route 13, five miles east of Seoul. Due to its construction of eleven supports and fifteen spans, this bridge is capable of carrying heavy vehicles."
    2222 "The single track rail line crosses the Han-gang at a fork where it becomes the Bughan-gang River."
    2223 "Two bridges cross the Bughan-gang River at separate points. A bridge at Kapyong carries the double track rail-line and the road crossing is further upriver near Chuncheon. Expanses of forest cover the area."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    2224 "This small wooden rail bridge is situated in a slightly hilly area just west of Chonui. This bridge has two support struts and five spans."
    2225 "Four bridges cross the Han-gang River to the South-east of Seoul; three steel cantilever bridges serve the main rail-line and a concrete highway bridge slightly further to the east handles heavy traffic.\n\nHistorical Note:\nOne bridge earned the title 'Elastic Bridge' due to its refusal to fall."
    2226 "Sinuiju is the most important gateway into North Korea. It is heavily defended with coverage from AAA on the Chinese bank of the Yalu. MiGs flying from four main bases just over the river can enter Korean air space in a matter of minutes."
    2227 "Xx"
    2228 "Sonchon is a supply-center connected by rail to Sinanju, north of the Chongchon River."
    2229 "Sakchu is situated near the Yalu River and it is home to the North Korean Military Academy."
    2230 "Chosan is a supply gateway located near the Yalu River.\n\nHistorical Note:\nROK troops arrived here on 26 Oct.1950 - shortly before the Chinese invaded."
    2231 "Xx"
    2232 "Chongjin has two major harbors, a railway yard and workshops. The shattered ruins of the Mitsubishi Iron company are here."
    2233 "No info available."
    2234 "No info available."
    2235 "Hamhung is an important port on the East Coast. It sends supplies throughout the region. The docks are an important military asset.\n\nHistorical Note:\nUN troops were evacuated from the docks during the Chinese advance in December 1950."
    2236 "Manpo is one of three gateway cities into North Korea. Supplies are brought here then filtered out to the supply dispersal points."
    2237 "Home to a large arsenal and communication center."
    2238 "This is a supply dispersal point."
    2239 "Historical Note:\nFollowing the UN advance into Pyongyang on 19 Oct. 51, the 187th Airborne RCT parachuted into a drop zone at Sukchon with the aim of cutting off retreating NKPA troops."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    2240 "Xx"
    2241 "The Capital and Arsenal of North Korea has armament plants, large freight yards and major railway plants."
    2242 "This port has anchorage for ships of any draft.\n\nHistorical Note:\nIn the opening stages of hostilities UN medium bombers destroyed the various metal production plants located here."
    2243 "Xx"
    2244 "Sariwon has a supply depot connected to Pyongyang by rail track."
    2245 "Xx"
    2246 "Historical Note:\nKaesong was the site of the first cease-fire conferences from 10 July to 2 August 1951. They later resumed at nearby Panmunjom following charges and counter-charges of neutrality violations."
    2247 "Wonsan is a major seaport and one of the three most important rail-hubs in Korea.\n\nHistorical Note: It was the main site for petroleum refining in North Korea before the start of hostilities."
    2248 "Kumhwa has a vital supply depot and also holds one of three major Communist Communications Centers.\n\nHistorical Note:\nKumhwa, along with Pyonggang and Chorwon, formed an area that came to be known as 'The Iron Triangle'."
    2249 "No info available."
    2250 "This town sits on a vital lateral supply link that runs from the west coast to the east.\n\nHistorical Note:\nThis area was so well defended that it came to be known as 'Death Valley' by pilots."
    2251 "Historical Note:\nPyonggang was the Northern most point of an area that was named 'The Iron Triangle' due to a good supply network to the rear and good defensive positions to the front. Kumhwa and Chorwon form the other two points that mark the region."
    2252 "Xx"
    2253 "Xx"
    2254 "When communist forces operate south of the 38th parallel, the focal point of their distribution system is Seoul. It is believed that around two thirds of all supplies pass through here.\n\nHistorical Note:\nThe South's capital changed hands four times during the course of the war. By the spring of 1951 much of the city had been reduced to rubble."
    2255 "Xx"
END
