STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    2276 "Runway: 5500 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Average\n\nSinmak is the first airfield north of the 38th Parallel, supported by Sariwon and Anak."
    2277 "Runway: 4800 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Jet squadron\nFacilities: Poor\n\nHwangju is a small airfield located below Pyongyang."
    2278 "Runway: 4800 ft. Earth surface\nSupport: 3 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Good\n\nLocated in the North West of Korea, just south of the Yalu river.\n\nHistorical Note:\nSinuiju and Uiju were the only airfields in Korea to receive MiGs, the rest being kept out of action."
    2279 "Xx"
    2280 "Runway: 6000 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 2 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Average\n\nSunan is one of the larger Communist airfields and is well defended by AAA sites."
    2281 "Runway: 7200 ft. Concrete surface\nSupport: 3 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Excellent\n\nThe Antung Airfield Complex is one of the largest and most modern in China. It has a radar system used to vector its fighters. On a good day UN pilots patrolling the Yalu can see MiGs leaving Antung."
    2282 "Runway: 6800 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 3 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Good\n\nThis major Chinese airfield is not as advanced as its sister field, Antung. Few of the aircraft revetments are used. The Communists are confident that they are protected from UN air attack."
    2283 "Runway: 7000 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 2 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Average\n\nUiju, most northern of the Korean airfields, is well defended by radar-controlled flak and by more than fifty searchlights."
    2284 "Runway: 4800 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Jet squadron\nFacilities: Poor\n\nAnak has a short airstrip with a poorly maintained surface. Its limited facilities contain some aircraft revetments."
    2285 "Runway: 4200 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Poor\n\nLocated just above the 38th parallel. Only necessary repairs are made in order to keep the airfield serviceable."
    2286 "Runway: 6000 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Poor\n\nYongyu is located on the North West Coast of Korea, south of Sinanju"
    2287 "Runway: 6200 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Average\n\n"
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    2288 "Runway: 4800 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Poor\n\nThis short earth airstrip is under the protective umbrella of the three jet airfields - Namsi, Taechon and Saamcham."
    2289 "Runway: 5500 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 2 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Average\n\nTaechon is one of three important North Korean jet airfields, including Saamcham and Namsi."
    2290 "Runway: 5900 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 2 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Average\n\nNamsi, like Taechon and Saamcham, is one of three jet airfields. The airfield plays an important role along side Taechon and Saamcham in the Chongchon area."
    2291 "Runway: 5700 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 2 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Average\n\nSimilar in size and facilities to its sister airfields, Namsi and Taechon, Saamcham plays an important role in the Chongchon area."
    2292 "Runway: 4000 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities:    Average\n\nLocated north-east of Pyongyang City. The airstrip has reasonable facilities with protective revetments for the aircraft."
    2293 "Runway: 4800 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Jet squadron\nFacilities:     Excellent\n\nPyongyang Main is the biggest of the three airfields at Pyongyang. The North Korean Air Force Headquarters are located nearby in the city."
    2294 "Runway: 5760 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Poor\n\nThis is an ingenious use of resources. A downtown street has been demolished to create a concrete runway. Support facilities are housed in the residential area with side streets acting as taxi-ways."
    2295 "Runway: 6400 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 3 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Excellent\n\nThe South's International Airport is the largest and most modern in Korea.\n\nHistorical Note:\nDuring the course of the war it changed hands many times. When it wasn't being demolished, it was being expanded by UN engineers."
    2296 "Runway: 4000 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Poor\n\nThis small earth airstrip is generally neglected when the facilities at nearby Kimpo are available."
    2297 "Runway: 4000 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Average\n\nChuncheon has a small clay and gravel runway. The airfield is primarily used to aid supply drops for front line troops."
    2298 "Runway: 9000 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 1 Jet squadron\nFacilities: Excellent\n\nHistorical Note:\nThis airfield was greatly upgraded by UN engineers over a period of years"
    2299 "Runway: 5000 ft. Concrete\nSupport: 2 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Average\n\nHistorical Note:\nSuwon was practically rebuilt by UN engineers over the course of three years."
    2300 "Runway: 5500 ft. Earth strip with PSP\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Average\n\n"
    2301 "Runway: 4800 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 1 Jet squadron\nFacilities: Average\n\nThis small airfield is found on the West Coast of Southern Korea near the port of Kunsan."
    2302 "Runway: 5200 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Poor\n\nDue to the dirt surface and poor drainage the airfield is only capable of supporting larger transports when the ground is frozen."
    2303 "Runway: 5300 ft. Clay and Gravel with PSP\nSupport: 2 Jet squadrons\nFacilities: Average\n\nTaegu's clay and gravel based runway assumes a new importance when enemy forces push below the 38th parallel. It is the rear-most jet capable field in Korea. Beyond that, jets must fly from Japan."
END
STRINGTABLE DISCARDABLE
BEGIN
    2304 "Runway: 3500 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Poor\n\n"
    2305 "Runway: 4600 ft. Dirt surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Average\n\nKangnung is located on the East Coast of Korea."
    2306 "Runway: 5000 ft. PSP\nSupport: 1 Jet squadron\nFacilities: Average\n\nLocated on the south east coast near the fishing village of Pohang. The surrounding area has been drained to allow for taxiways and other extra facilities."
    2307 "Runway: 6000 ft. Hard surface\nSupport: 1 Prop squadron\nFacilities: Average\n\n"
